      "layout": "The page primarily uses a full-bleed layout for hero sections, filling the viewport horizontally. Content sections then generally narrow to a contained maximum width, centered on the page. The hero features a large full-bleed image with centered overlaid text. Sections follow a consistent vertical rhythm with a 60px gap. Content is arranged in alternating patterns, often with large image cards followed by text blocks. There's a clear 4-column implied grid for card layouts, though some sections use a single dominant image. Navigation is a minimalist top bar, sticky or otherwise. The overall density is comfortable, allowing for strong visual impact from images and typography.",
      "imagery": "This design system primarily utilizes photography, which is often full-bleed and serves as the dominant visual element. Images are usually high-contrast and often moody, presented with raw, un-masked edges and no rounding. Product shots are contained within image cards, and lifestyle photography in hero sections is used to set the tone rather than provide explicit information. Icons are minimal, likely outlined and monochromatic, acting as functional cues rather than decorative elements. Image density is high, with visuals often taking precedence over text in content blocks.",
